            <title>[KAFKA-15010] KRaft Controller doesn&apos;t reconcile with Zookeeper metadata upon becoming new controller while in dual write mode.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-15010</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a KRaft controller fails over, the existing migration driver (in dual write mode) can fail in between Zookeeper writes and may leave Zookeeper with incomplete and inconsistent data. So when a new controller becomes active (and by extension new migration driver becomes active), this first thing we should do is load the in-memory snapshot and use it to write metadata to Zookeeper to have a steady state. We currently do not do this and it may leave Zookeeper in inconsistent state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
